{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb5f92d18-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s297i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"297i"},"text":"§ 297i.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Procedures for appeal of terminations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In any case in which the Secretary intends to terminate an agreement with a school of nursing under this part, the Secretary shall provide the school with a written notice specifying such intention and stating that the school may request a formal hearing with respect to such termination. If the school requests such a hearing within 30 days after the receipt of such notice, the Secretary shall provide such school with a hearing conducted by an administrative law judge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb5f92d19-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title VIII, § 842, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/92/s8/g"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–92, § 8(g)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-08-16"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/399"},"text":"99 Stat. 399","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tV/s5310/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title V, § 5310(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/631"},"text":"124 Stat. 631","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb5f92d1a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes